HEADWORD: Thirty-second
<hw>Thir"ty-sec`ond</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Being one of
thirty-two equal parts into which anything is divided.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Thirty-second note</b></col> <fld>(Mus.)</fld>, <cd>the
thirty-second part of a whole note; a demi-semiquaver.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

